headline: Robinson scores 20 to lift Fresno State over Southern Utah
recap: FRESNO, Calif. -- — Orlando Robinson had 20 points as Fresno State beat Southern Utah 67-48 in The Basketball Classic semifinals on Monday night.
Jordan Campbell had 11 points for Fresno State (22-13).
Maizen Fausett had nine points for the Thunderbirds (23-12).

headline: Williams lifts Coastal Carolina over South Alabama in OT
recap: MOBILE, Ala. -- — Rudi Williams sank a 3-pointer with one second remaining in overtime to lead Coastal Carolina to a 69-68 win over South Alabama in The Basketball Classic semifinals on Monday night.

Williams had 17 points on 8-of-10 shooting to lead the Chanticleers (19-13). Vince Cole had 16 points, Essam Mostafa added 12 points and four assists, and Ebrima Dibba had eight points and 10 rebounds.
Javon Franklin had 17 points and 12 rebounds for the Jaguars (21-12). Tyler Shirley added 14 points and Alex Anderson had 10 points.
